The Bank of England said it invited anearly round of bill offers to help ease tight conditions in themoney market.    The bank estimated today's liquidity shortage at about 1.10billion stg.    Bills maturing in official hands and the treasury billtake-up would drain 1.21 billion stg from the system while arise in the note circulation and below target bankers' balanceswould take out 265 mln and 180 mln respectively, the bank said.    Against this, exchequer transactions would add a net 535mln stg. REUTER&#3;